cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of automatic image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves statistical tests and dynamic programming, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the global properties of the produced segmentation, which is related to graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, experiments are conducted on real natural images, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
